{
  "id": "019d286a-f2d7-7750-81b8-3308d38d2cc5",
  "content": "## Retriever Implementations\n\n### VectorRetriever\n\nPure vector search with visibility filtering. Equivalent to what `ContextBuilder` does today.\n\n```\nembed(query) → store.search(limit * 2) → RBAC filter → visibility filter → take(limit)\n```\n\n\n### GraphExpandRetriever\n\nVector search + graph edge expansion. Corvia's differentiator.\n\n```\nembed(query) → store.search(top-k)\n    → for each result: graph.edges(entry_id, Outgoing, depth)\n    → collect expanded entries via store.get()\n    → deduplicate (by entry ID)\n    → score: final = (1 - α) * cosine_score + α * (1.0 / (hop_distance + 1))\n    → RBAC filter → visibility filter → sort by final_score → take(limit)\n```\n\n`α` is configurable (default 0.3 — vector-dominant with graph boost). Entries found only via graph get a base cosine score of 0.0 for blending.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-02-m3.2-rag-pipeline-design.md",
